data.title: Liberty University Flames

data.text:
2022 (R-Fr.):

Saw playing time in all 13 games

Served as Liberty’s starting kicker for field goals and extra points

Finished the season connecting on 11-of-19 field goals

Was a perfect 3-of-3 on field goals from 40 to 49 yards

Knocked down 40-of-41 extra point attempts

Led the Flames in scoring with 73 points

Scored eight or more points in six games

Knocked down a pair of field goals, including one in overtime, during Liberty’s season-opening four-overtime win at Southern Miss

Scored a season-best 11 points during Liberty’s victory over BYU

Finished the BYU game 2-of-2 on field goal attempts and knocking down all five extra point attempts

2021 (Fr.):

Redshirted in 2021 after playing in one game

Prep:

Graduated from Centennial High School in Frisco, Texas

Special Teams MVP during his junior and senior seasons

Second-Team All-District honoree as a junior

Finished his junior season 26-of-26 on PATs and 9-of-10 on field goals

First-Team All-District honoree as a senior

Finished his senior season 38-of-40 on PATs and 5-of-6 on field goals

20 touchbacks as a senior

Also played soccer

Personal:

Son of Stephanie and Michael Brown

Business Administration major

Birthday is on February 20
